ime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Recommended Grit Progression For Bare Wood Projects</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 21 Nov 2025 03:27:43 +0000</pubDate><category>Wood sanding</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit progression</category><category>clear coat</category><description>Learn the best grit progression for bare wood. Clear steps, tool tips, and finish-specific advice to get smooth, even surfaces and professional results.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="grit-progression-for-bare-wood-a-practical-guide"&gt;Grit Progression for Bare Wood: A Practical Guide&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The shop is quiet except for the low thrum of the dust collector warming up. A mug of coffee cools on the bench while you run your fingertips across a fresh board—straight from the planer, faint ridges under the grain. Last time, you started too fine and paid for it with stubborn tear-out lines that only became visible after stain. This time you want a better plan. You want a clear grit progression that fits the wood, the project, and the finish you’ve chosen.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/21.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/facebook/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/facebook/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/facebook/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/instagram/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/instagram/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/instagram/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/pinterest/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/pinterest/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/pinterest/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/facebook/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/facebook/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/21/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression/cards/facebook/recommended-grit-progression-for-bare-wood-projects-grit-progression.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>How To Level Uneven Wood Panels By Sanding Only</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 10 Nov 2025 14:29:42 +0000</pubDate><category>Wood sanding</category><category>grit-60</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-500</category><category>sanding block</category><category>dust control</category><category>grit progression</category><description>Learn pro sanding techniques for surface leveling. Flatten uneven wood panels by hand—no planer, no drama. Tools, grits, tips, and fixes from a pro.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="surface-leveling-sanding-uneven-wood-panels-flat"&gt;Surface Leveling: Sanding Uneven Wood Panels Flat&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On a cool Saturday morning, your glue-up looks perfect from three paces away. The seams are tight, the grain lines match, and you’re already picturing the finish. Then the raking light hits—tiny ridges, a clamp bump here, a cup there. You run a straightedge across and hear that hollow tick in the middle. No planer, no drum sander, and only the shop basics on your bench. This is where the craft begins, not where it ends. With deliberate handwork, smart tool choice, and disciplined grit progression, you can achieve precise surface leveling using sanding alone. The key is to treat the panel like a system: track where the highs are, remove stock only where you must, and lock in flatness before you chase scratches. If your project is an heirloom tabletop or a cabinet door set, your workflow doesn’t change much—what changes is your patience and how clearly you can “see” the surface as you sand. I’ll show you my repeatable process for flattening panels by hand, with nothing more than sandpaper, a few blocks, and a healthy respect for dust control and measurement. You’ll learn to read the wood, choose the right grit sequences, and avoid common traps like rolling edges or leaving a subtle dish that ruins your finish. This is hands-on, no-nonsense surface leveling tailored for real shops and real projects.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/facebook/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/facebook/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/facebook/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/instagram/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/instagram/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/instagram/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/pinterest/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/pinterest/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/pinterest/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/facebook/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/facebook/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/10/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling/cards/facebook/how-to-level-uneven-wood-panels-by-sanding-only-surface-leveling.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>9</readingTime></item><item><title>Raise The Grain With Water Before Final Sanding</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 04 Nov 2025 13:36:49 +0000</pubDate><category>Wood sanding</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-320</category><category>grit-1000</category><category>grit progression</category><description>Engineer-tested methods for grain preparation: why wet-raising wood before final sanding improves stain uniformity and surface smoothness.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="grain-preparation-raise-the-grain-before-final-sanding"&gt;Grain Preparation: Raise the Grain Before Final Sanding&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first time I watched a walnut tabletop go from silky-smooth to prickly in minutes, I winced. I had sanded carefully through the grits, vacuumed, inspected under raking light—then I misted it with water. Within ten minutes, tiny “whiskers” stood up across the surface like a five o’clock shadow. If you’re new to this, the instinct is to panic. But as a product engineer who spends days measuring scratch patterns, fiber deformation, and finish adhesion, I’ve learned that moment is when control begins. What looks like backtracking is actually the most reliable path to a level, refined finish. It’s the heart of grain preparation.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/facebook/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/facebook/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/facebook/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/instagram/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/instagram/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/instagram/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/pinterest/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/pinterest/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/pinterest/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/facebook/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/facebook/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/04/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation/cards/facebook/raise-the-grain-with-water-before-final-sanding-grain-preparation.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>How To Sand Wood Without Swirl Marks</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 02 Nov 2025 18:31:25 +0000</pubDate><category>Wood sanding</category><category>wet sanding</category><description>Discover expert tips on wood sanding to avoid swirl marks. Enhance your DIY projects and achieve a flawless finish with our detailed guide.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="mastering-wood-sanding-avoiding-swirl-marks"&gt;Mastering Wood Sanding: Avoiding Swirl Marks&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woodworking is more than just a hobby—it&amp;rsquo;s a passion. Picture this: the soft glow of morning light streaming through your workshop window, the smell of freshly cut wood filling the air, and the satisfying hum of your sander as you work on your latest project. You’re sanding a beautiful oak table, envisioning the perfect smooth finish that will make your craftsmanship shine. But as you wipe away the dust, you notice the dreaded swirl marks marring the surface. It’s a common frustration among woodworkers, both novice and seasoned, but it doesn’t have to be your reality.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/instagram/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/instagram/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/instagram/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/pinterest/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/pinterest/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/pinterest/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/02/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-sand-wood-without-swirl-marks-wood-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>6</readingTime></item></channel></rss>